HEADWORD: Brasque
<hw>Brasque</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.]</ety>
<fld>(Metal.)</fld> <def>A paste made by mixing powdered charcoal, coal,
or coke with clay, molasses, tar, or other suitable substance. It is
used for lining hearths, crucibles, etc. Called also
<altname>steep</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Brass</ent>⟦br⟧
